You can also add assertions to jQuery about the length of the chain:<p>jQuery.fn.assertLength = function(i) {
    if (this.length != i) {
        throw "Expected " + i + " matching elements, selection was: " + this.get();
    }
    return this;
}<p>If you're using jQuery 1.3 (with its new selector property), a better implementation might be:<p>jQuery.fn.assertLength = function(i) {
    if (this.length != i) {
        throw "Expected " + i + " matching elements, got " + this.length + ", selector was: " + this.selector;
    }
    return this;
}<p>You can then introduce the assertLength method in to your chains like so:<p>$('div#intro a').assertLength(3).click(...)<p>If the number of matched elements doesn't match the expected, you get a descriptive exception raised which stops execution and shows up in the error console.
